<a name="overview"></a>
===== Overview =====

The 45Drives Firmware Update system allows administrators to check for and apply firmware updates to HBAs and NICs directly from the Cockpit web interface. Updates are served from a central firmware repository managed through the Admin UI.

**Note:** This release supports flashing HBA and NIC firmware only. HDDs and other device types are discovered and displayed for informational purposes but cannot be flashed from the UI at this time.

**Components:**

  * **Cockpit UI**
    * End-user interface for viewing and applying firmware updates.
    * Access it at %%https://<server-ip>:9090/%%.
  * **Admin UI**
    * Administrative interface for managing firmware files, models, and manifests.
    * Access it at %%http://<admin-ip>:8089/%%.
  * **firmware-check**
    * Background script that discovers hardware and compares against the latest manifest.
  * **firmware-flash**
    * Script that downloads and applies firmware to a specific device.

==== Access Notes ====

  * Access to the Cockpit UI requires a valid user account on the server.
  * Access to the Admin UI may require your IP address to be whitelisted by an administrator.

<a name="logging_into_cockpit"></a>
===== 1. Logging into Cockpit =====

  - Open your browser and go to %%https://<server-ip>:9090/%%.
  - Enter your username, typically ''root'', and password.
  - Click **Log In**.

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:01-login.png?direct |Login Page}}

<a name="navigating_to_the_firmware_section"></a>
===== 2. Navigating to the Firmware Section =====

  - In the left sidebar, click **45Drives System**.
  - The System Overview page loads showing server details, including model, serial, CPU, and memory.
  - Scroll down to the **Firmware** section.

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:11-system-overview.png?direct |System Overview}}

<a name="firmware_updates_available"></a>
===== 3. Firmware Updates Available =====

When firmware updates are detected, a banner displays available updates and device details.

==== Screens ====

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:12-multiple-updates.png?direct |Multiple Updates Available}}

==== Fields ====

  * **Firmware Updates Available**
    * Shows the count of outdated devices.
  * **Type**
    * Device category, such as HBA, NIC, or HDD. Only HBA and NIC devices can be flashed in this release.
  * **Device**
    * Model name and identifier.
  * **Current FW**
    * Currently installed firmware version.
  * **Latest FW**
    * Newest available version from the repository.
  * **Actions**
    * Update button and Info button.
  * **Last checked**
    * Timestamp from the most recent firmware check.

==== Options ====

  * **Update**
    * Flash a single device (HBA and NIC only).
  * **Info**
    * Open detailed information for the selected device.

<a name="viewing_device_information"></a>
===== 4. Viewing Device Information =====

Click the **Info** button next to any device to see detailed information.

==== Screens ====

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:15-firmware-info-dialog.png?direct |Device Info Dialog}}

==== Fields ====

  * **Device type**
    * HBA, NIC, or HDD.
  * **Model and family**
    * Hardware model and matched firmware family.
  * **PCI address or drive path**
    * Hardware location used by the firmware tooling.
  * **Current firmware**
    * Firmware version currently installed on the device.
  * **Latest firmware**
    * Newest firmware version available in the repository.
  * **Flash tool**
    * Tool used to apply the firmware, such as ''storcli64'', ''niccli'', or ''SeaChest''.
  * **Firmware file**
    * Repository firmware file name.
  * **SHA256**
    * Firmware integrity hash.

<a name="updating_a_single_device"></a>
===== 5. Updating a Single Device =====

==== Workflow ====

  - Click the **Update** button next to the device you want to update.
  - Review the confirmation dialog.
  - Type ''confirm flash'' in the text field to enable the Proceed button.
  - Click **Proceed**.
  - Monitor the flash log until the operation completes.

==== Confirmation Dialog ====

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:20-confirm-dialog-empty.png?direct |Confirmation Dialog - Empty}}

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:21-confirm-dialog-filled.png?direct |Confirmation Dialog - Filled}}

The confirmation dialog shows:

  * Device name and type
  * Firmware version transition
  * Safety disclaimer and maintenance window recommendation
  * Confirmation text field (type ''confirm flash'' to enable the Proceed button)
  * Proceed and cancel actions

==== Flash Progress ====

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:22-flash-in-progress.png?direct |Flash In Progress}}

The flash log streams in real time and may show:

  * Firmware file download progress
  * Flash tool execution output
  * Success or failure result

==== Result ====

{{ :rnd:rnd:rhans:firmwareupdate:24-single-flash-complete.png?direct |Single Flash Complete}}

Once complete, the result displays:

  * **Success**
    * Firmware was applied.
  * **Failed**
    * Firmware was not applied and an error reason is shown.

==== Video Walkthrough ====

  * [[videos/firmware-flash-demo-final.mp4|firmware-flash-demo-final.mp4]]



<a name="reboot_after_flashing"></a>
===== 6. Reboot After Flashing =====

After flashing HBA or NIC firmware, a reboot is typically required.

==== Behavior ====

  * A **Reboot Required** banner appears at the top of the page.
  * Click **Safe Reboot** to initiate a controlled reboot.
  * After reboot, the device shows the updated firmware version.

==== Important ====

  * HBA and NIC updates always require a reboot for the new firmware to take effect.
  * Perform reboots during a scheduled maintenance window.

<a name="troubleshooting"></a>
===== 7. Troubleshooting =====

^ Issue ^ Possible Cause ^ Solution ^
| No firmware updates shown | ''firmware-check'' has not run yet | Wait for the scheduled check or trigger it manually. |
| Firmware file not found error | File is missing from the firmware repository | Verify that the file exists on the admin server. |
| Flash fails with ''REFUSED'' | Current firmware version is not compatible with the upgrade path | Check the ''upgrade_from'' field in the manifest. |
| Reboot banner will not clear | Reboot has not been performed yet | Click **Safe Reboot** or reboot the server manually. |

